def: The capacity, on the part of one of the parents, as comparedwith the other, to transmit more than his or her own share ofcharacteristics to their offspring.
A nontoxic diamine, C4H12N2, formed in the putrefaction of theflesh of mammals and some other animals.
The state of being an ape.
Chemical action taking place through an intervening membrane.
Happening or done every hour; occurring hour by hour; frequent;often repeated; renewed hour by hour; continual.In hourly expectation of a martyrdom. Sharp.
The act of weakening; enervation; weakness.
An aliquant part of a number or quantity is one which does notdivide it without leaving a remainder; thus, 5 is an aliquant part of16. Opposed to aliquot.
An artifical division of vertebrates, including those that layeggs; -opposed to Vivipara.
Homogenous; -- applied to that class of homologies which arisefrom similarity of structure, and which are taken as evidences ofcommon ancestry.
To take up; to elevate; to assume. [Obs.] Sheldon.
Having the power or quality of shaking or agitating. Johnson.
